               <p>WILLIAM WAY. I am a <rs id="t18281023-160-viclabel954" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-160-victim875 t18281023-160-viclabel954"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18281023-160-crimeloc955">North Audley-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-160-crimeloc955" type="placeName" value="North Audley-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-160-crimeloc955" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-160-off952 t18281023-160-crimeloc955"></join>. On the 11th of October, about ten minutes past seven o'clock, my son told me something; I went out, and saw the prisoner about two doors from me, with the leg of mutton - I caught him by the collar, and brought him back; he threw down the mutton in the next door-way - it was mine, and I had hung it just outside my shop about a quarter of an hour before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-160-person876">
                  WILLIAM 
                  WAY, JUN
               <interp inst="t18281023-160-person876" type="surname" value="WAY, JUN"></interp>
